50|$|Laddering also {{describes}} a process where, in order <b>to</b> <b>purchase</b> <b>shares</b> {{at a given}} price, investors must also agree <b>to</b> <b>purchase</b> additional <b>shares</b> at a higher price. This artificially inflates {{the price of the}} stock and allows insiders to buy at the lower price, with a guarantee {{that they will be able}} to sell at a higher price. This practice has resulted in investigations of national and global banks by the SEC after the stock market collapse.|$|R
