50|$|In May 2008, comScore {{announced}} its acquisition of M:Metrics, a company measuring mobile content consumption. The transaction involved a cash payment of $44.3 million {{and the issue}} of approximately 50,000 options <b>to</b> <b>purchase</b> <b>shares</b> of comScore common stock to certain M:Metrics unvested option holders.|$|R
